# Publications split pipeline

- **Source of truth:** `book/cv/publications.md` (the numbered list under `# Publications`). Generated files must start with YAML frontmatter (`---` on line 1). Do not put an HTML comment above the first `---`, or MyST will not parse `title` and will show `title: ...` on the page.
- **Generated (do not edit by hand):** `book/cv/publications-healthcare-labor-economics.md`, `book/cv/publications-substance-use-disorder.md`, `book/cv/publications-institutional-economics.md`, `book/cv/publications-education-teaching-economics.md`, `book/cv/publications-veterans-health.md`, `book/cv/publications-strategic-analysis.md`. They are produced by `scripts/generate_publications_md.py` and are checked in pre-commit and CI.
- **Veterans Health** and **Strategic Analysis** are overlapping filters (not exclusive with the four primary themes). Adjust `VETERANS_HEALTH_KEYWORDS` and `STRATEGIC_ANALYSIS_KEYWORDS` in the script if classification is wrong.
- After editing `publications.md` or the script, run:

```bash
python scripts/generate_publications_md.py
```

- The generator uses keyword rules to assign items to four themes (SUD is separate from healthcare; entries containing `opioid` go to SUD). If classification is wrong, adjust keywords in the script or the source list, rather than hand-editing generated files.
